@page "/about"

<SeoHead Title="About Enigma | Evolving Puzzle Maze Game"
         Description="Learn what Enigma is, how map discovery works, and why the game blends evolving puzzle mazes, co-op play, and a player-driven map economy."
         OpenGraphType="article"
         SchemaType="Article"
         Keywords="Enigma game, puzzle maze game, about Enigma, maze discovery game" />

<div class="content seo-page-shell">
    <section class="panel seo-page-hero">
        <span class="profile-kicker">About</span>
        <h1>What Is Enigma?</h1>
        <p>Enigma is a puzzle maze game built around discovery, ownership, and live systems. Players run solo or co-op expeditions, collect and trade maps, assign maps to analysis for daily rewards, and shape decisions through council voting.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>What Makes Enigma Different</h2>
        <p>Enigma treats mazes as collectible game objects. A successful run can become a persistent map with its own art, value, owner, founder, and history. Those maps feed a player-driven economy with listings, analysis rewards, and governance influence.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Core Systems</h2>
        <h3>Single-Player Runs</h3>
        <p>Generated and saved mazes use room-specific puzzle locks, timed runs, and permanent loss if the player abandons a real maze.</p>
        <h3>Co-op Sessions</h3>
        <p>Two players can run a synchronized expedition with live invites, shared room progression, ready checks, and coordinated finish conditions.</p>
        <h3>Economy and Governance</h3>
        <p>Maps can be listed, sold, analyzed for daily MN, and used to strengthen council vote weight. Voting sessions are bank-controlled while all players can participate when voting is open.</p>
        <h3>Profiles and Presence</h3>
        <p>Profiles track activity, map ownership, staked-map totals, and online presence so player interactions are visible across the app.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Explore More</h2>
